   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To recover local knowledge of sustainable farming practices that have been lost or suppressed by years of operating under the dominant model of conventional agriculture and market pressures. Local families and trained technicians of MST-PE will work together to create a demonstration unit that will serve as a training ground for settlement residents and can be replicated in other settlements. In addition to agriculture, the project includes raising Creole chicken varieties, considered more resistant to diseases and better adjusted to the local drought-prone environment</narrative>
